$***********************$ * Precious Lord, take my hand Lead me on, let me stand I'm tired, I'm weak, I'm lone Through the storm, through the night Lead me on to the light Take my hand, precious Lord Lead me home
$***********************$ 1. When my way grows drear Precious Lord, linger near When my light is almost gone Hear my cry, hear my call Hold my hand, lest I fall Take my hand precious Lord Lead me home
$***********************$ 2. When the darkness appears And the night draws near And the day is past and gone At the river, I stand Guide my feet, hold my hand Take my hand precious Lord Lead me home

